# Custom Elements Pattern

Key requirements:
- Use shadow DOM with `attachShadow({ mode: "open" })` in constructor
- Create template element outside the class with encapsulated styles
- Clone template content into shadow root: `this.shadowRoot!.appendChild(template.content.cloneNode(true))`
- Follow naming convention: `[ElementName]CustomElement` class → `<element-name>` tag
- Include JSDoc comments with `@customElement` tag

See `app/icons/play/index.ts` and `app/components/AlbumImage/album-image-custom-element.ts` for examples.

Use https://github.com/webcomponents/gold-standard/wiki as a baseline for quality

## JSDoc standard

Every custom element class must have a JSDoc block that includes all of the following:

1. **`@customElement` tag** with the registered HTML tag name
2. **HTML usage example** (`@example` with a fenced `html` block) showing the element with its key attributes
3. **TypeScript example** (`@example` with a fenced `typescript` block) for any element that dispatches events or exposes a JS API
4. **`## Attributes` section** — one `###` subsection per observed attribute, documenting its type, accepted values, and behaviour. Mark required attributes explicitly.
5. **`## Events` section** — one `###` subsection per dispatched `CustomEvent`, including whether it bubbles/is composed and the full `detail` shape as a fenced `typescript` block
6. **`## Slots` section** — if the element uses `<slot>` in its template
7. **`## Properties` section** — if the element exposes a public JS API (getters/setters beyond attributes)

Reference implementation: `app/components/Tracklist/tracklist-item-custom-element.ts`